description.narrative: Output 5.4: Strategies to address cross-cutting issues related to child rights are developed and applied, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral - Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change, Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Innovation, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 5 - Programme Effectiveness: Country programmes are efficiently designed, coordinated, managed and supported to meet quality programming standards for achieving results for children

description.narrative: COVID-19 pandemic impact on communities shaped the C4D work throughout the year. Despite challenges associated with restricted movement, C4D contributed to outcomes;across sections by applying social and behaviour change strategies. Knowledge attitudes and practices (KAP) and social data were generated for Violence Against Children (VAC), civil registration, back to School, and impact of COVID-19 on adolescent girls and cross-border population. Four rounds of immunization campaigns, VAC-campaigns, and disability inclusion campaign raised awareness among the target population to take up the services extended with UNICEF support. Government and partners capacity were strengthened for development and humanitarian context to deliver C4D intervention. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:04/01/2022
